5. Challenges of Manual Carving

5.1 Fragmentation
	•	Files split across disk
	•	Requires:
	•	Fragment identification
	•	Reconstruction logic
	•	Handling missing segments

⸻

5.2 Time Complexity
	•	Large datasets (GB–TB)
	•	Manual scanning is slow

⸻

5.3 Technical Barriers
	•	Corrupted headers
	•	False positives
	•	Proprietary formats
	•	Encryption

⸻

5.4 Core Insight

Manual carving =
High precision + high effort

