7. Scenario 3: Deleted File Recovery (Foremost & Scalpel)

7.1 Observation
	•	Mounted disk shows:

lost+found



→ Appears empty but contains unallocated data

⸻

7.2 Foremost

Command:

foremost -i Challenge3_deleted_disk.img -o output_dir -c /etc/custom_foremost.conf

Key Features:
	•	Scans entire disk
	•	Uses config file:
	•	File types
	•	Headers/footers
	•	Max file size

⸻

Targeted Extraction:

foremost -t pdf,jpg,png -i Challenge3_deleted_disk.img -o output_dir


⸻

7.3 Scalpel

Command:

scalpel Challenge3_deleted_disk.img -o ScalpelOutput -c /etc/scalpel/scalpel.conf

Process:
	1.	First pass → identify boundaries
	2.	Second pass → extract files

⸻

7.4 Foremost vs Scalpel

Feature	Foremost	Scalpel
Speed	Moderate	Faster
Config	Flexible	Similar
Fragment handling	Limited	Slightly better


